  10:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * Support for I2S Audio Protocol with different bit-depth, samplerate options
  11:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * Allows for master or slave, as well as freedom of selecting direction, 
  12:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * and other behavior for each peripheral, and block.
  13:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * 
  14:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * DMA Transfer commands must use buffers located within non-cached memory or use cache maintenance
  15:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * To declare an unitialized global element in the DMA memory section:
  16:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  *    int32_t DSY_DMA_BUFFER_SECTOR my_buffer[96];
  17:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  *
  18:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * Callback functions will be called once per half of the buffer. In the above example, 
  19:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * the callback function would be called once for every 48 samples.
  20:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * 
  21:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * Use SAI Handle like this:
  22:/Users/reza.kalfane/Workspaces/Daisy/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * 
